Stan Lee, the man who dreamt up Spiderman, Iron Man and The Hulk (and many others) died at the age of 95 on November 12. Comic fans have taken to social media to praise the superhero boss and pay tribute to how he changed their childhoods. Marvel-inspired memes have been dominating social media as fans say goodbye to the iconic Lee. Funeral arrangements have yet to be announced. South African celebrities have also paid tribute to Lee, posting message of their comic memories.